  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">supporting 100 Farmer suicide families in India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers, the food producers are victims of perpetual agrarian crisis. Widows become farmers when husbands commit suicides, forced to shoulder family responsibilities to take care of children education, aged family members and survive in farming. In addition gender discrimination and sexual abuse is facing very often. FIAN empower and council widow farmers community to rehabilitate ,  face challenges and stand on their own in finding livelihood and compensation from the Government.</narrative>
  </description>
